Kim Jong Il Inspects Company of KPA Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected a company of KPA Unit 669 honored with the title of O Jung Hup-led 7th regiment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After acquainting himself with the company's performance of duty, he dropped in at the military lecture room to learn about how combat training is conducted at the company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He praised the company for preparing its soldiers as a-match-for-a hundred fighters possessed of a high level of military technique and combat capability by successfully building the military lecture room and organizing effective training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he paid deep attention to the service and living of the soldiers, making the rounds of an education room, a bedroom, a mess hall, a kitchen, a non-staple food store, a barn and other places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After learning about how the company conducts its political work, he underscored the need for it to conduct a variety of ideological education in an appealing, plain and amusing manner to suit the characteristics of the young soldiers, including an oratorical meeting, a gathering for giving impressions of the books read and a meeting for congratulating exemplary soldiers. He taught ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the successes made by the soldiers of the company, pleased to learn that they are leading a life full of revolutionary and militant spirit after successfully sprucing up their revolutionary post. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photograph taken with the servicemen of the company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su.

Kim Jong Il Inspects Women's Company of KPA Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected a women's company of KPA Unit 1374. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He acquainted himself with the company's performance of duty and appreciated the efforts made by its soldiers, expressing satisfaction over the fact that they are performing their combat duty with vigilance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he learned in detail about the service and living of the soldiers, going round an education room, a bedroom, a mess hall, an outdoor resting place, a barn and other places of the company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pleased very much to see the soldiers leading a happy life free from any inconvenience, he expressed great satisfaction over the fact that the company has provided them with good living conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is good that the soldiers of the company are preparing themselves as stalwart women revolutionaries, voluntarily observing the steel-strong discipline, he said, adding that no period is as noble and worthwhile as the days spent by one as a soldier with arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He saw the pencil drawings done by Choe Hyon Chun, a young soldier of the company, and highly appreciated her art talent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Very laudable are the women soldiers who are assiduously managing their economic life by their own efforts, he noted, stressing that the company is, indeed, a school for perfecting human beings in the era of Songun as it helps the soldiers not only acquire a revolutionary world outlook but cultivate patriotism, comradeship, precious life experience and diligence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He highly appreciated the signal achievements made by the soldiers of the company in the past, saying that it set an example in all aspects including its management. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the soldiers of the company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su.

Bird Flu Differential Method Established in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- Researches for a strict and prompt prevention of possible outbreak and spread of bird flu have carried out in the DPRK, which have culminated in some significant successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Scientists of the Branch Academy of Cell and Gene Engineering under the State Academy of Sciences have collected and classified analytical data on thousands of viruses belonging to various subtypes which have been confirmed and publicized in the world in recent years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
On this basis, they have laid a scientific and technological foundation for an easy and accurate differentiation of subtypes of HA bird flu viruses from 1 to 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
On the other hand, they have established a scientific and technological method of quickly differentiating NA subtypes from 1 to 9, which are more difficult to differentiate than HA subtypes because of the scarcity of confirmed data and their excessive variability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Now they are making confirming experiments on a high standard in contact with relevant units.

Brisk Activities in Months for Water Sports in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- The DPRK has set July and August as months for water sports to train the body and mind of the people through swimming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A large number of working people of all walks of life and school youth and children are taking an active part in water sports activities at bathing resorts and swimming pools built in seas, rivers and streams in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Various areas including Songdowon and Thongchon of Kangwon Province and Majon of South Hamgyong Province which face the sea are making an effective use of the sea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Panwoldo Swimming Pool in Pyongyang is crowded with thousands of swimming fans every day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
River-crossing contests are frequently taking place in the regions with rivers so as to raise people's interest in and zeal for swimming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Swimming is also positively encouraged in schools across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The schools in cities and counties of Ryanggang, Jagang and North Hwanghae provinces with many mountains and rivers have built open-air swimming pools with mountain stream and river water to teach swimming skill and basic knowledge to students. They also often hold swimming contests between classes and same grades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Middle school and college students are striving to have an ability of swimming hundreds of meters. The number of classes and schools whose students have hit this goal is ever increasing.

Exploit of Kim Il Sung in Building Socialist Country Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- It is the greatest exploit of President Kim Il Sung for the people that he built a socialist paradise in this land by applying the idea of believing in the people as in Heaven, Rodong Sinmun Monday says in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the DPRK is a history in which the President's idea of believing in the people as in Heaven has been embodied, and our country could shine all over the world as a genuine socialist country thanks to his great politics of love for the people, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatness of the President in building the people-centered socialist country can be found in the fact that he set forth all lines and policies reflecting the aspiration and demand of the people and successfully implemented them while sharing the mind and will with the people to break through all difficulties and ordeals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His greatness is also manifested in that he made all the gains of the revolution shine as treasures of eternal value for the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President always put forward the people as master of politics in every period and at every stage of building the country and regarded it as an iron rule to advance any line and policy reflecting aspiration and demand of the people. That is why all the lines and policies of the Workers' Party of Korea have always displayed their great vitality, winning absolute support and sympathy from all the people and socialist construction in the DPRK could advance along the road of victory without any turns and twists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In every hard time, the President trusted in people and gave confidence in sure victory and courage to them to bring about great upsurge. His leadership made it possible to create a heroic epic about miracles of Chollima Korea and helped the DPRK emerge a socialist power independent in politics, self-supporting in the economy and self-reliant in national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Regarding it as his greatest pleasure to always go among the people, he would make an endless journey to visit them in disregard of weathers or red-letter days. This journey resulted in great happiness of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our socialist country built by the President is the cradle of eternal life and happiness of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are the most dignified people as they have enjoyed happiness and comfort generation after generation in the powerful and prosperous socialist country centered on the popular masses under the guidance of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the miracle of history that a strong springboard for building a great prosperous powerful nation was provided and the era of great prosperity opened up in this land thanks to the leadership of Kim Jong Il who has devoted his all to prosperity of the country associated with the whole life of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, the glorious motherland founded by Kim Il Sung and led by Kim Jong Il, is, indeed, the cradle of the Korean people's independent life and happiness and the banner of victory and prosperity.

All Koreans Called upon to Work for National Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- It is the most vivid manifestation of patriotism and the most sacred national duty which all Koreans assumed before history and the generations to come to struggle for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a by-lined article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to achieve national reunification it is necessary for the Koreans to fully realize the unity of the nation, putting aside all differences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If national unity is to be achieved, all the classes and strata and organizations within the nation should, first of all, refrain from prioritizing their interests and pursuing partisan interests and strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No sooner had the Lee Myung Bak group of south Korea come to power than it cried out for recovering the "lost decade." It has viciously opposed the reconciliation and unity of the nation and national reunification and worked with bloodshot eyes to bring back the era of inter-Korean confrontation in collusion with outside forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality goes to prove that to insist on one's ism in utter disregard of the will and wishes of the nation and to seek partisan interests and strategy would only lead to antagonism and confrontation between fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans in the north and the south and abroad should actively turn out in the struggle for national reconciliation and unity and reunification, keenly aware of their historic mission to achieve national reunification despite manifold ordeals and difficulties and bring about the unity of the whole nation on the principle of subordinating everything to the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea of "By our nation itself" precisely means a banner for national unity. The validity and vitality of the idea have been clearly proved in the reality of the June 15 era of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whoever is a member of the Korean nation should find the worth and pride of leading a true human life in working hard to realize the desire of the fellow countrymen for reunification. Every Korean, no matter where and what he or she does, should make a tangible contribution to the cause of national reunification as the one responsible for it.

Imperialism Bound to Go to Decline and Ruin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- It is an immutable law of the development of history that imperialism is bound to go to decline and ruin as it is the leftover of the old era and doomed as the refuse of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Imperialism is rapidly going to decline and ruin. This finds a vivid manifestation in the bankruptcy of its policy of aggression and war and the new change that has taken place in the balance of forces in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists' policy of aggression and war is meeting a failure and frustration in face of the struggle of the people to carve out their destinies independently, taking a firm grip on them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The balance of forces in the world has turned more favorable to the side of the revolution, the side of forces for progress and independence and the anti-imperialist independent forces have grown definitely stronger than the imperialist reactionary forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialist process of going to decline and ruin can find its expression in the serious economic crisis sweeping the capitalist world. The article cites the following facts to prove this: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Due to the deepening economic crisis, the political crisis and social contradictions have grown more acute in the capitalist countries and the rivalry among the imperialist powers to secure markets and expand the sphere of their influence is getting fiercer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Western countries are getting more undisguised in their "trade war" and "oil dispute" to meet their interests by sacrificing other countries and confrontation and clash surrounding the international monetary crisis are festering. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-imperialist independent forces, the mainstream of the era, are winning one victory after another while the imperialist reactionary forces are being driven to a tight corner, hit hard by the people.  Nothing can stop imperialism from going to decline and ruin just as it can never turn back the wheel of history.

Program for August 15 Event Announced in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- Representatives of civic and public organizations in south Korea including the Solidarity for Progress and the South Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration on August 7 inaugurated the Committee for Promoting the August 15 Meeting for National Reunification and announced its action program. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the inaugural ceremony held in Seoul that day speakers said that the said meeting would be focused on the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration and the realization of peace on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that during the period of the meeting they would make public the August 15 declaration on national independence, hold a national rally vowing the struggle against the distortion of history and for liquidation of the colonial remnants and defence of Tok Islet and conduct August 15 grand march and cultural event for independence and sovereignty and thus demonstrate the Korean nation's will for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 August 15 will mark the 100th day since the candlelight actions were launched against the import of American beef, they noted, stressing that the promotion committee would vigorously conduct the movement against Japan's shameless moves for grabbing Tok Islet and the Lee Myung Bak group's confrontation policy towards the DPRK, holding the slogan "Turn candlelight against mad cow disease into candlelight for national dignity and independence and sovereignty!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal read out at the ceremony underlined the need to clearly show the spirit of national independence to the flunkeyist traitors who are selling off the people's right to existence, yielding to foreign forces. It called upon all the people to turn out as one in the work to ensure the successful holding of the August 15 meeting.

Military Authorities' Anti-Reunification Moves Flayed in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- Recently the south Korean puppet military authorities defined as "seditious books" 23 kinds of books praising the DPRK and calling for the stand against the U.S. and the "government" and blocked their dissemination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard, publishing businesses and authors concerned are staging a protest against such behavior after forming a joint measure committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint measure committee held an emergency meeting on August 5 and strongly denounced the anti-reunification and treacherous behavior of the Defense Ministry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization declared that it would conduct vigorous activities including legal countermeasure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In a statement issued on August 7 it noted that the publication and dissemination of books calling for national reunification and opposition to the U.S. had been banned under the past military fascist dictatorial regimes. It deplored the reality that such acts are being openly committed in the present era of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It demanded that the military authorities open to the public the details about how the list of "seditious books" was made and the standard of definition and immediately stop such poor and inhumane behavior and make an official apology to the people.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona compania femenina de unidad no. 3407 de EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 11 de agosto (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea inspecciono la compania femenina que ostenta la Bandera Roja de las Tres Revoluciones adscrita a la unidad no. 3407 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras ver el entrenamiento de las militares de la compania el Dirigente se entero en la sala del servicio de guardia del estado de cumplimiento de esta mision. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Expreso satisfaccion de que las militares de la compania con la sublime conciencia de que la defensa de la patria es el maximo patriotismo defienden su puesto con el estado de alerta y de disposicion  combativa y cumplen satisfactoriamente su deber combativo e indico las tareas que se presentan para fortalecer mas la combatividad de la compania. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Acto seguido recorrio la sala de educacion, el dormitorio, el comedor, el bano, el deposito de alimentos subsidiarios y otros lugares de la compania. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Pregunto minuciosamente si no hay descomodidades para la vida de las uniformadas que se ponen de guardia durante la estacion veraniega bochornosa, no hay humedad en el dormitorio, como se elaboran los alimentos subsidiarios y si se realiza regularmente la vida cultural para averiguar los detalles del conjunto de la labor y vida de las soldadas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Estuvo alegre de que las oficiales acondicionaron bien la compania y ofrecieron magnifica condicion de vida a las soldadas y evaluo sus esfuerzos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tambien evaluo altamente sus exitos logrados diciendo que esta compania que sostiene con fidelidad la politica de Songun (priorizacion militar) del partido hace esmeradamente la administracion de la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente Kim Jong Il se fotografio junto con las militares de la compania. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le acompanaron los generales de ejercito del EPC Hyon Chol Hae y Ri Myong Su.
